PSL Chairperson Irvin Khoza is expected to brief the media on Thursday at the League’s headquarters in Johannesburg. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. PARKTOWN - PSL Chairperson Irvin Khoza is expected to brief the media on Thursday at the league’s headquarters in Johannesburg. Khoza is expected to focus on a wide range of issues that plague the domestic league. From the Mamelodi Sundowns case, Icasa, NFD side Tshakhuma ignoring rule of using under-23 players and deaths of PSL players in car accidents. On Wednesday, at the Icasa hearings, Khoza warned that if the league was to be prevented from selling its broadcast rights on an exclusive basis, it would run into poverty.